words: It was in eighth grade, and there was a girl that I had had a crush on for, y'know, about a year or two.
And we were good friends, but had never been anything more than that. She had been with a boy for,
uh, a couple of months or maybe a year, um, before me.
Um, but one night, my friend was having a party, and a few days before, um, as, I
guess, eighth graders do or did, we planned, we called each other and talked, and
we planned that we would mutually, y'know, hook up at this party. Um,
so I was really excited because I, obviously, I liked her a lot. But then a couple
hour before the party, my friend called me and said he had heard that she had hooked up with her, her old boy,
um, the old guy that she had been hooking up with before, the night before at a different
party. Um, so I called her, and I confronted her about it, and she said, "No, I have no idea
what he's talking about. That didn't happen. Like, we went out and talked, but y'know, we never hooked up." And
I believed her. Um, so that was okay. And so, the next night, or that night,
we, we hooked up at this party, I was really happy about it. Um, her friends kept
texting me, asking me how it was. I, I got really excited. I thought maybe, y'know, there was a future there,
um, in terms of dating her and stuff. Um, I would then find out that,
later that night, she had snuck out of her house and had hooked up with this boy that
she had, in fact, hooked up with the night before, as well, and lied about both of those events to my face,
um, for quite a while afterwards. Um, it was only, probly a couple of weeks after
it happened that she actually admitted it to me. And, being lied to like that,
um, y'know, had a really big effect on me. I didn't do anything
with girls for a couple years after because I was so hurt by it, and I was so scared of kind of getting hurt again.
Um, I did actually end up dating this girl in high school for about a year and a half, so eventually it worked out,
and I was able to get over it. But at the time, it was really, really devastating for me, and I, I really lost trust,
